def replacement(text,remove_units=False):
    
    for word in replace_dict.keys():
        text = text.replace(word,replace_dict[word])
    
    # delete "," in the middle of numbers (for thousands)
    text = re.sub(r"(\d)[,](\d)",r"\1\2",text)
    
    # replace the "." of numbers
    text = re.sub(r"(\d)[.](\d)",r"\1p\2",text)
    
    # replace feet by ft, only when there is a number before
    text = re.sub(r'(\d+) *feet',r'\1ft',text)
    text = re.sub(r'(\d+) *inch',r'\1in',text)
    text = re.sub(r'(\d+) *cu[.]? +ft',r'\1cuft',text)
    text = re.sub(r' +cu[.]? +ft',r' cuft',text)
    text = re.sub(r'(\d+) *sq[.]? +ft',r'\1sqft',text)
    text = re.sub(r' +sq[.]? +ft',r' sqft',text)
    text = re.sub(r'(\d+) *sq[.]? +in',r'\1sqin',text)
    text = re.sub(r' +sq[.]? +in',r' sqin',text)
    text = re.sub(r'(\d+) *ft[.]? +lbs',r'\1ftlbs',text)
    text = re.sub(r' +ft[.]? +lbs',r' ftlbs',text)
    text = re.sub(r'(\d+)-watt',r'\1watt',text)
    text = re.sub(r'(\d+)-volt',r'\1v',text)
    text = re.sub(r'(\d+)-v ',r'\1v ',text)
    text = re.sub(r'(\d+)-amp',r'\1amp',text)
    text = re.sub(r'(\d+)-degree',r'\1deg',text)
    text = re.sub(r'(\d) +pcent',r'\1pcent',text)
   
    if remove_units:
        for unit in units:
            text = re.sub(r'(\d+) *'+unit+'[. ]+',r'\1 ',text)
            text = re.sub(r' +'+unit+'[.]? +',' ',text)
    else:
        # remove the space between a number and a unit
        for unit in units:
            text = re.sub(r'(\d+) *'+unit+' +',r'\1'+unit+' ',text)
        
    # replace "by" by "x" when between 2 sizes
    text = re.sub(r'(\.+) +by +(\d+)',r'\1 x \2',text)
    
    # transform sequence such as "5 in. W x 10 in. D x 5 in. H"  ->  5in x 10in x 5in
    text = re.sub(r'(\d+\w*)[.]? *[lwdh][.]? *x *(\d+\w*)[.]? *[lwdh][.]? *x *(\d+\w*)[.]? *[lwdh][.]?',r'\1 x \2 x \3',text)
    text = re.sub(r'(\d+\w*)[.]? *[lwdh][.]? *x *(\d+\w*)[.]? *[lwdh][.]?',r'\1 x \2',text)
    
    text = re.sub(r'(\d+\w*) *x *(\d+\w*)',r'\1 x \2',text)
    text = re.sub(r'(\d+\w*) *x *(\d+\w*) *x *(\d+\w*)',r'\1 x \2 x \3',text)
    
    # Regroup structures like "R 19" or "r-19" into "r19" (excluding "x")
    text = re.sub(r'^([a-wyz])[- ]+(\d)',r'\1\2',text)
    text = re.sub(r' +([a-wyz])[- ]+(\d)',r' \1\2',text)
    
    # if something is "not included", remove it
    text = re.sub(r'[-(,]+ +[\w+ ]+ not included *[).-]*',r' ',text)
    
    text = re.sub(r' - ',r' ',text)
    text = re.sub(r' / ',r' ',text)
    
    text = re.sub('^coke ',r'cocacola ',text)
    
    return text

Deal with punctuation¶

In [396]:
# define a punctuation set where there is no "-","%","/"
punctuation_subset = '!"#$&\'()*+,.:;<=>?@[\\]^_`{|}~'

# define a table that would replace punctuation by a space
table = str.maketrans(punctuation_subset, ' '*len(punctuation_subset))

def replace_punctuation(text):
    return text.translate(table)

def preprocess(text,param=preprocess_default_param):
    text = text.lower()  # lowercase
    text = replacement(text,remove_units=param['remove_units'])  # pretreat the data
    text = replace_punctuation(text) # remove punctuation
    tokens = nltk.word_tokenize(text) 
    tokens = remove_stop_words(tokens) # remove stopwords
    return ' '.join(stem_tokens(tokens))

def str_common_word(str1,str2):
    return sum(int(str2.find(word)>=0) for word in str1.split())

def preprocess_data(data):
    print('Preprocessing search terms...')
    data['search_term'] = data['search_term'].map(lambda x:preprocess(x))
    print('Preprocessing product title...')
    data['product_title'] = data['product_title'].map(lambda x:preprocess(x))
    print('Preprocessing product description...')
    data['product_description'] = data['product_description'].map(lambda x:preprocess(x))
    print('Preprocessing done.')
    return data

# build ngrams from list of words
def ngrams(text,n):
    input_list = str(text).split()
    return list(zip(*[input_list[i:] for i in range(n)]))

def try_divide(a,b,val=0.0):
    if b !=0. :
        val = float(a)/b
    return val
In [414]:
def build_counting_features(data):
    
    # query ngrams
    print('....Build search ngrams...')
    print('........unigrams')
    data['search_unigrams'] = data['search_term'].map(lambda x:ngrams(x,1))
    print('........bigrams')
    data['search_bigrams'] = data['search_term'].map(lambda x:ngrams(x,2))
    print('........trigrams')
    data['search_trigrams'] = data['search_term'].map(lambda x:ngrams(x,3))
    
    # title ngrams
    print('....Build title ngrams...')
    print('........unigrams')
    data['title_unigrams'] = data['product_title'].map(lambda x:ngrams(x,1))
    print('........bigrams')
    data['title_bigrams'] = data['product_title'].map(lambda x:ngrams(x,2))
    print('........trigrams')
    data['title_trigrams'] = data['product_title'].map(lambda x:ngrams(x,3))
    
    # description ngrams
    print('....Build description ngrams...')
    print('........unigrams')
    data['description_unigrams'] = data['product_description'].map(lambda x:ngrams(x,1))
    print('........bigrams')
    data['description_bigrams'] = data['product_description'].map(lambda x:ngrams(x,2))
    print('........trigrams')
    data['description_trigrams'] = data['product_description'].map(lambda x:ngrams(x,3))
    
    # count unigrams
    print('....Count n-grams')
    for feat_name in feat_names:
        for gram in grams:
            data['count_of_%s_%s' % (feat_name,gram)] = data['%s_%s' % (feat_name,gram)].map(lambda x:len(x))
            data['count_of_unique_%s_%s' % (feat_name,gram)] = data['%s_%s' % (feat_name,gram)].map(lambda x:len(set(x)))
            data['ratio_of_unique_%s_%s' % (feat_name,gram)] = data.apply(lambda x:try_divide(x['count_of_unique_%s_%s' % (feat_name,gram)],x['count_of_%s_%s' % (feat_name,gram)]),axis=1)
    
    return data

def count_word_in_set(words,word_list):
    return sum([1 for word in words if word in set(word_list)])

def build_intersect_features(data):
    
    for gram in grams:
        print('    for search')

        data['ratio_search_%s_in_title' % (gram)] = data.apply(lambda x:try_divide(x['count_search_%s_in_title' %gram],x['count_of_search_%s'%gram]),axis=1)
        data['count_search_%s_in_description' %gram] = data.apply(lambda x:count_word_in_set(x['search_%s'%gram],x['description_%s' % gram]),axis=1)

        print('    for title')
        data['count_title_%s_in_search' % gram] = data.apply(lambda x:count_word_in_set(x['title_%s'%gram],x['search_%s' % gram]),axis=1)

        data['count_title_%s_in_description' % gram] = data.apply(lambda x:count_word_in_set(x['title_%s'%gram],x['description_%s' % gram]),axis=1)

        print('    for description')
        data['count_description_%s_in_search' % gram] = data.apply(lambda x:count_word_in_set(x['description_%s'%gram],x['search_%s' % gram]),axis=1)

        data['count_description_%s_in_title' % gram] = data.apply(lambda x:count_word_in_set(x['description_%s'%gram],x['title_%s' % gram]),axis=1)

    return data

Distance features¶

In [417]:
def JaccardCoeff(A,B):
    if len(A)>0: 
        A=A[0]    
    else:
        A=[]
    if len(B)>0:
        B=B[0]
    else:
        B=[]
    a = set(A)
    b = set(B)
    intersect = len(a.intersection(b))
    union = len(a.union(b))
    return try_divide(intersect,union)
In [418]:
def build_distance_features(data):
    for gram in grams:
        for i,target_name in enumerate(feat_names[:-1]):
            for obs_name in feat_names[i+1:]:
                print("    Jaccard_of_%s_between_%s_%s" % (gram,target_name,obs_name))
                data["Jaccard_of_%s_between_%s_%s" % (gram,target_name,obs_name)] = data.apply(lambda x: JaccardCoeff(x[target_name+'_'+gram],x[obs_name+'_'+gram]),axis=1)
    return data

def get_brand_names(attr_data):
    brand_names = attr_data[attr_data['name']=='MFG Brand Name']['value'].apply(lambda x:preprocess(str(x)))
    
    remove = ["wall",'natur', 'innov', 'applic', 'industri']
    brand_names = [brand for brand in brand_names if not brand in remove]
    
    return set(brand_names)


def brand_in_text(text,brands):
    """find if there are brands in the text"""   
    # search if there are some brands in the bag of words
    token = set(text.split())
    
    brand_list = []
    for brand in brands:
        if brand in token:
            brand_list.append(brand)
    return brand_list


def brand_in_common(text1,text2,brands):
    brand_list1 = set(brand_in_text(text1,brands))
    brand_list2 = set(brand_in_text(text2,brands))
    return len(brand_list1.intersection(brand_list2))

def build_brand_features(data):
    
    data['count_brand_in_search'] = data.apply(lambda x:len(brand_in_text(x['search_term'],brand_names)),axis=1)
    data['count_brand_in_title'] = data.apply(lambda x:len(brand_in_text(x['product_title'],brand_names)),axis=1)
    data['count_brand_in_description'] = data.apply(lambda x:len(brand_in_text(x['product_description'],brand_names)),axis=1)
    
    data['ratio_brand_in_search'] = data.apply(lambda x:try_divide(x['count_brand_in_search'],x['count_of_search_unigrams']),axis=1)
    
    data['count_brand_in_search_title'] = data.apply(lambda x:brand_in_common(x['search_term'],x['product_title'],brand_names),axis=1)
    data['ratio_brand_in_search_title'] = data.apply(lambda x:try_divide(x['count_brand_in_search_title'],x['count_brand_in_search']),axis=1)
    data['count_brand_in_search_description'] = data.apply(lambda x:brand_in_common(x['search_term'],x['product_description'],brand_names),axis=1)
    data['ratio_brand_in_search_description'] = data.apply(lambda x:try_divide(x['count_brand_in_search_description'],x['count_brand_in_search']),axis=1)
    
    data['count_brand_in_search_title_or_description'] = data.apply(lambda x:x['count_brand_in_search_title']+x['count_brand_in_search_description'],axis=1)
    data['ratio_brand_in_search_title_or_description'] = data.apply(lambda x:try_divide(x['count_brand_in_search_title_or_description'],x['count_brand_in_search']),axis=1)
    
    return data

from itertools import chain

def get_materials(attr_data):
    material_attr = attr_data[attr_data['name']=='Material']['value'].apply(lambda x:preprocess(str(x)))
    
    # make some replacement
    material_attr = [mat.replace('/','') for mat in material_attr]
    material_names = material_attr
    
    # remove numbers and percentages
    material_names = [re.sub('\d+pcent',' ',mat) for mat in material_names]
    material_names = [re.sub('\d+',' ',mat) for mat in material_names]

    material_names = [m.split() for m in material_names]

    material_names = set(list(chain.from_iterable(material_names)))
    
    remove_list = ['manufactur','100pcent','16mm','materi','medium','high','densiti','fiberboard']
    for item in remove_list:
        if item in material_names:
            material_names.remove(item)
    
    return material_names

def material_in_text(text,materials):
    """find if there are materials in the search query"""   
    # search if there are some materials in the bag of words
    token = set(text.split())
    
    material_list = []
    for material in materials:
        if material in token:
            material_list.append(material)
    return material_list

def material_in_common(text1,text2,materials):
    material_list1 = set(material_in_text(text1,materials))
    material_list2 = set(material_in_text(text2,materials))
    return len(material_list1.intersection(material_list2))
    

def material_match(row):
    
    material_list = material_in_search(row,materials)
    
    if len(material_list)==0:
        return 0
    else:
        count = 0
        title_unigrams = set(row['title_unigrams'])
        description_unigrams = set(row['description_unigrams'])
        for material in material_list:
            if (material in title_unigrams) or (material in description_unigrams):
                count+=1
        return count
In [444]:
def build_material_features(data):
    
    data['count_material_in_search'] = data.apply(lambda x:len(material_in_text(x['search_term'],materials)),axis=1)
    data['count_material_in_description'] = data.apply(lambda x:len(material_in_text(x['product_description'],materials)),axis=1)
    data['count_material_in_title'] = data.apply(lambda x:len(material_in_text(x['product_title'],materials)),axis=1)
    
    data['ratio_material_in_search'] = data.apply(lambda x:try_divide(x['count_material_in_search'],x['count_of_search_unigrams']),axis=1)
        
    data['count_material_in_search_title'] = data.apply(lambda x:material_in_common(x['search_term'],x['product_title'],materials),axis=1)
    data['ratio_material_in_search_title'] = data.apply(lambda x:try_divide(x['count_material_in_search_title'],x['count_material_in_search']),axis=1)
    data['count_material_in_search_description'] = data.apply(lambda x:material_in_common(x['search_term'],x['product_description'],materials),axis=1)
    data['ratio_material_in_search_description'] = data.apply(lambda x:try_divide(x['count_material_in_search_description'],x['count_material_in_search']),axis=1)
    
    data['count_material_in_search_title_or_description'] = data.apply(lambda x:x['count_material_in_search_title']+x['count_material_in_search_description'],axis=1)
    data['ratio_material_in_search_title_or_description'] = data.apply(lambda x:try_divide(x['count_material_in_search_title_or_description'],x['count_material_in_search']),axis=1)
    
    return data

def build_features(data):
    
    # build counting features
    print('Counting features:')
    data = build_counting_features(data)
    
    # build intersect features
    print('Intersect features:')
    data = build_intersect_features(data)
    
    # distance features
    print('Distance features:')
    data = build_distance_features(data)
    
    # build features based on attributes
    print('Attributes features')
    data = build_attr_features(data)
    
    return data

min_RMSE = 1
best_param = []

for n_estimators in params['n_estimators']:
    for max_features in params['max_features']:
        for depth in params['max_depth']:
            for min_samples_leaf in params['min_samples_leaf']:
                print('N_EST: %d ; MAX_FEAT: %d ; MAX_DEPTH: %d ; MIN_SAMPLE: %d' % (n_estimators,max_features,depth,min_samples_leaf))
                # define random forest
                rf = RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=n_estimators,max_features=max_features,max_depth=depth,random_state=0,n_jobs=-1,min_samples_leaf=min_samples_leaf)
                #clf = BaggingRegressor(rf,n_estimators=45,max_samples=.1,random_state=25)
                clf = rf
                
                # use k-fold cross validation
                y_pred = cross_validation.cross_val_predict(clf,X_train,y_train,cv=5,verbose=1)

                # calculate RMSE
                RMSE = mean_squared_error(y_train, y_pred)**0.5
                print("RMSE: %0.7f" % (RMSE))

                if RMSE<min_RMSE:
                    min_RMSE = RMSE
                    best_param = { 'n_estimators' : n_estimators,
                                   'max_features': max_features,
                                    'max_depth' : depth,
                                    'min_samples_leaf' : min_samples_leaf
                    }

Apply model on test data¶

For memory reason, we split the test data in smaller shunks and do the preprocessing, features building and prediction on each split

In [535]:
def apply_model(model,raw_data,features):
    # preprocessing
    data = preprocess_data(raw_data)
    
    # build features
    data = build_features(data)
    
    # select features
    columns = data.columns.tolist()
    drop_list = [col for col in columns if col not in features]
    data = data.drop(drop_list,axis=1)
    
    # use model to predict result
    print('Prediction...\n')
    X = data.values
    y = model.predict(X)
    
    return y

for i,split in enumerate(row_split):
    print('SPLIT %d' % i)
    y = apply_model(clf,df_test[split[0]:split[-1]+1].copy(),selected_features)
    result_list.append(y)
    
y_pred = np.hstack(result_list)
